# Project Overview

- Vue 3.5 project using Composition API with <script setup>
- Do not import new libraries without approval
- Use ES imports, not require()
- Tailwind CSS 4.1 styles framework.

# Design System

- Tokens: colors, spacing, shadows, z-index, transitions, theme
- Base: fonts, reset, typography, animations
- Themes: light, dark

## Usage Guidelines

- No px units (use rem)
- No CSS comments
- No BEM notation
- Use CSS nesting and semantic class names

## Project description

The project implements a responsive administrative panel for the REST API Python project <https://github.com/GregoryGost/gost-rdpr>
The openapi.json description is in the file TARGET_OPENAPI.md

No authorization

The visual part of the project consists of:

- A header displaying the logo as an image and text
- A left menu with buttons for navigating through sections
- A central block to the right of the left menu displaying the main content
- A footer with standard information about the project author, the current year, and copyright symbol, as well as links to the author's blog, social media accounts, and repository.
- Repeating text values ​​should be output to variables that are recorded in the constants.ts file.

Menu items and content block contents depending on the selected menu:

- Home - displays key numeric indicators
- DNS Servers - displays information about entered DNS servers
- Domains - displays information about domain lists and the domains themselves
- IP Addresses - displays information about IP address lists and the IP addresses themselves
- Configurations - displays information about entered configurations
- Commands - allows you to send commands for configurations

All sections (except the Home page) not only display information but also allow you to add or delete it.

Information is displayed in a tabular format with pagination.
You can select the number of elements to display simultaneously. When selected, the pagination changes accordingly.
